uction. At x0 the function \u03a8(x) has the same discontinuity as in the standard 1D case, because for the direct\n\ntrajectory Lp = x\u2212x0 has a jump in its derivative.", "embedding": [-0.0016416997, 0.022693146, 0.032925434, 0.028012598, -0.03692955, -0.024859848, -0.0007105363, -0.0137685165, -0.037152924, 0.10961486, 0.05625045, 0.02854749, -0.0015353524, -0.014108712, -0.00033009122, 0.03355587, -0.0031045794, -0.043630186, -0.046159677, 0.0011418404, 0.026177887, 0.0069246604, -0.048869032, -0.026764119, -0.028388297, 0.019680494, -0.005875787, 0.0011279172, 0.041953735, 0.016171463, 0.0486562, -0.009311518, 0.016402991, -0.061684564, 0.023841316, 0.005537735, 0.031431146, -0.022853225, 0.020236423, -0.024636146, 0.031539433, 0.0031509686, -0.011093995, -0.0031099217, 0.010144986, -0.03303854, -0.03847166, 0.020063234, -0.023565266, -0.03252391, -0.009243197, 0.017523168, -0.009494793, -0.04289815, -0.046948653, 0.012642608, 0.0313959, -0.0018772725, -0.039118264, 0.016797878, 0.009477839, -0.035350338, 0.027445897, -0.0511215, 0.012422656, 0.045087315, -0.02388224, 0.04164277, 0.029693944, -0.020972315, -0.01594269, -0.008613606, 0.005345825, 0.0055592605, -0.009500307, 0.052101284, 0.018181551, -0.04049804, -0.03011003, 0.008046002, -0.020058291, -0.0350889, -0.055579506, 0.040166438, -0.02574488, -0.0068056174, -0.01121059, 0.0155366855, 0.018193137, 0.015791185, 0.047755055, 0.057159692, -0.020148607, 0.0010350241, 0.034175947, 0.054396003, -0.005229642, 0.0147517305, -0.007918756, 0.026833136, 0.018287605, 0.06744329, -0.037453406, 0.044215586, -0.029023679, 0.05201909, 0.00313918, 0.03980096, -0.018047083, -0.04029319, 0.005807336, -0.01041987, 0.02544014, 0.0101222275, -0.012459603, 0.015806075, 0.023573974, -0.025218915, -0.019292265, -0.016751707, -0.011565733, 0.007358202, 0.048530206, 0.007497726, -0.016245067, -0.019056391, -0.025886511, 0.007687938, -0.036872763, -0.018700516, 0.020720514, -0.021288307, -0.01175197, 0.027216641, 0.0030478914, 